## BQ24297 I2C Read API Refactor -- Implementation Plan

### Problem Statement

`BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg)` returns `uint8_t` with `0xFF` as the error sentinel. Since `0xFF` is a valid register value (e.g., REG09 with all fault bits set, REG0A part number), callers cannot reliably distinguish errors from legitimate data. The write function `BQ24297_Write_I2C` already returns `bool`, so the read function is the odd one out.

### New Signature

```c
// Old:
uint8_t BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg);

// New:
bool BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg, uint8_t *out);
// Returns true on success (data written to *out), false on I2C error.
```

### Files Affected (3 files total, plus documentation)

1. `/mnt/c/Users/User/Documents/GitHub/daqifi-nyquist-firmware/firmware/src/HAL/BQ24297/BQ24297.h` -- declaration + doxygen
2. `/mnt/c/Users/User/Documents/GitHub/daqifi-nyquist-firmware/firmware/src/HAL/BQ24297/BQ24297.c` -- implementation + ~24 internal call sites
3. `/mnt/c/Users/User/Documents/GitHub/daqifi-nyquist-firmware/firmware/src/services/SCPI/SCPIInterface.c` -- ~13 external call sites

### Step-by-Step Implementation

---

#### STEP 1: Change the function implementation (BQ24297.c, line 412-446)

Change the function body at line 412:

```c
// FROM (line 412):
uint8_t BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg) {
    uint8_t I2CData[1];
    uint8_t rxData = 0;
    if (pData->I2C_Handle == DRV_HANDLE_INVALID) {
        LOG_E("BQ24297_Read_I2C: Invalid I2C handle");
        return 0xFF;
    }
    if (i2cMutex != NULL) { xSemaphoreTake(i2cMutex, portMAX_DELAY); }
    I2CData[0] = reg;
    bool success = DRV_I2C_WriteReadTransfer(...);
    if (i2cMutex != NULL) { xSemaphoreGive(i2cMutex); }
    if (!success) {
        LOG_E("BQ24297_Read_I2C: Failed to read register 0x%02X", reg);
        return 0xFF;
    }
    return rxData;
}

// TO:
bool BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg, uint8_t *out) {
    uint8_t I2CData[1];
    uint8_t rxData = 0;
    if (pData->I2C_Handle == DRV_HANDLE_INVALID) {
        LOG_E("BQ24297_Read_I2C: Invalid I2C handle");
        return false;
    }
    if (i2cMutex != NULL) { xSemaphoreTake(i2cMutex, portMAX_DELAY); }
    I2CData[0] = reg;
    bool success = DRV_I2C_WriteReadTransfer(...);
    if (i2cMutex != NULL) { xSemaphoreGive(i2cMutex); }
    if (!success) {
        LOG_E("BQ24297_Read_I2C: Failed to read register 0x%02X", reg);
        return false;
    }
    *out = rxData;
    return true;
}
```

---

#### STEP 2: Update the header declaration (BQ24297.h, line 293) and forward declaration (BQ24297.c, line 25)

**BQ24297.h line 289-293:**
```c
// FROM:
/*!
 * Read a BQ24297 register via I2C
 * @param[in] reg Register address to read
 * @return Register value or 0xFF on error
 */
uint8_t BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg);

// TO:
/*!
 * Read a BQ24297 register via I2C
 * @param[in] reg Register address to read
 * @param[out] out Pointer to receive register value (unchanged on error)
 * @return true on success, false on I2C error
 */
bool BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg, uint8_t *out);
```

**BQ24297.c line 25 (forward declaration):**
```c
// FROM:
uint8_t BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg);
// TO:
bool BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg, uint8_t *out);
```

