    reg07Ok ? (batfetEnabled ? "Enabled" : "Disabled!") : "ERR",
    reg01Ok ? ... : "ERR",
    reg07Ok ? ... : "ERR");
```

Alternatively, keep the snprintf format the same but show 0x00 for failed reads (simpler, since this is informational). The current code does not check for 0xFF here at all -- using the new API forces us to handle the error, which is an improvement either way.

##### 4b. SCPI_GetBQRegisters loop, line 1043 -- Pattern: register dump loop

```c
// FROM (lines 1039-1045):
uint8_t regs[11];
int errCount = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 11; i++) {
    if (i == 9) continue;
