## Current State
`uint8_t BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg)` returns data or `0xFF` on error. ~28 call sites check `== 0xFF` to detect errors. But 0xFF is valid register data, so this is architecturally wrong.

`bool BQ24297_Write_I2C(uint8_t reg, uint8_t data)` already returns bool — this is fine.

## Goal
Change read to: `bool BQ24297_Read_I2C(uint8_t reg, uint8_t *out)` — returns true on success, data via pointer.

## Files to modify
1. `firmware/src/HAL/BQ24297/BQ24297.h` — declaration
2. `firmware/src/HAL/BQ24297/BQ24297.c` — implementation + 24 internal call sites
3. `firmware/src/services/SCPI/SCPIInterface.c` — ~10 external call sites (SCPI_GetBQRegisters, SCPI_SetBQILim, SCPI_ForceDPDM, SCPI_GetBQDiagnostics, plus SCPI_SystemInfo if present)

## Key patterns to handle

### Pattern 1: Read-only status (UpdateStatus, diagnostics)
```c
// Current:
regData = BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x00);
if (regData != 0xFF) { /* decode */ } else { hasErrors = true; }
// New:
if (BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x00, &regData)) { /* decode */ } else { hasErrors = true; }
```

### Pattern 2: Read-modify-write (ChargeEnable, SetIINLIM, etc.)
```c
// Current:
reg = BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x01);
if (reg == 0xFF) { return; }
reg = (reg & mask) | bits;
BQ24297_Write_I2C(0x01, reg);
// New:
if (!BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x01, &reg)) { LOG_E(...); return; }
reg = (reg & mask) | bits;
BQ24297_Write_I2C(0x01, reg);
```

### Pattern 3: SCPI register loop
```c
// Current:
for (int i = 0; i < 11; i++) {
    regs[i] = BQ24297_Read_I2C(i);
    if (regs[i] == 0xFF) errCount++;
}
// New:
for (int i = 0; i < 11; i++) {
    if (!BQ24297_Read_I2C(i, &regs[i])) { regs[i] = 0; errCount++; errors[i] = true; }
}
```

### Pattern 4: Polling loops (DPDM, ManageIINLIM)
```c
// Current:
status = BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x07);
if (status == 0xFF) { i2cOk = false; break; }
// New:
if (!BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x07, &status)) { i2cOk = false; break; }
```

### Pattern 5: Bug fixes needed — Config_Settings lines 133, 186
These sites currently have NO error check before RMW. The new API forces error handling:
```c
// Line 133 — REG00 RMW without error check:
reg = BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x00);
BQ24297_Write_I2C(0x00, reg & 0b00000111);  // If read failed, writes garbage
// Fix:
if (!BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x00, &reg)) { LOG_E(...); /* skip or use safe default */ }
```

### Pattern 6: EnableOTG lines 595-600 — reads without error check
```c
uint8_t reg08 = BQ24297_Read_I2C(0x08);
bool pgStat = (reg08 >> 2) & 0x01;  // 0xFF → pgStat=true, incorrect
```

